reviewBlob: Skunky, grassy, citrus aromas, the body is a mid orange with a thin head that leaves some spotty lace. Flavors of over -ripe grapefruit, lemons with a middle of the road bitterness. Overall its decent enough...

beerName: Boulevard Collaboration No. 5 Tropical Pale Ale
reviewBlob: A sediment filled mid orange body with a 1/2 inch speckled cap. Aroma of citrus, papaya, old mango. Flavor has the flavors of the fore mentioned aromas with some stale pineapple with a touch of alcohol towards the finish, overall its a bit off, maybe i have an old bottle.

beerName: BS Brewing Pecan Ale with Honey
reviewBlob: Murky Brown body with some sediment, the head is a thin soapy ring that is leaving some spotty lace. Aroma has plenty of pecan upfront with touches of vanilla and honey. Flavor is much the same as the aroma with some of the malts coming out, it finishes slightly dry with pecan oil.

Aroma as expected lots of ripe sour cherries, the body is brown with amber hues when held to the light, the thin white/ light tan head is full and frothy. Nice carbonation bite, its thankfully not overdone. The matiness starts and finishes in the flavor, the middle is all about the cherries. Overall a well rounded fruit beer.

Rich and complex aromas, with each sniff i pick up another aroma. Initially it was cocoa powder, dark chocolate and fresh coffee beans. As it warms the barrel is coming through- bourbon, vanilla, oak, and a touch of booze. Black body, plenty of carbonation feeding the pillowy tan cap, kinda surprised for a high ABV to see a head like this. Palate is thick and syrupy with a touch of carbonation. Taste is predominantly of the bourbon, with hints of vanilla, wood, chocolate, the bitter roastiness of the coffee is coming through. A big alcohol taste is noticeable but this is 17.5% so... A nice big beer, but the price would keep me from buying another.

Aromas, of course has the pineapple but also mango, grapefruit, tangerine, papaya with a touch of dank. Clear mid yellow body, the head is thin and soapy, but is leaving a fair amount of lace, medium palate a touch sticky but not bad. Flavor is pineapple heavy with tropical fruit and a medium bitter bite. Overall another good version of a great beer.

beerName: No Label Suburban Funk Cherry Sour
reviewBlob: A hazy mid orange/ yellow tinged body, no head only a few carbonation bubbles coming up. Aroma has cherries, vinegar, and a touch of barn yard. Flavor is much the same with the sourness of the cherries overtaking that flavor, a bit of feet on the backside.

Originally rated on 8/13/08. The 6th and final beer from the craft sampler case. Pale bock lives up to the name with a pale brown, heavily carbonated body with a thick head. Slight aromas of malt, flavor was light malts and nutty. Mouthfeel was watery. Overall it was decent, but i probably wouldnt buy it again.

Originally rated on 8/ 12/08. No. 5 out of the craft sampler case, the porter poured a black body; amber when held up to bright light. The mid tan head left some fair lacing, the aroma was faint, but the flavors of roasted malts, toffe, coffee and hints of chocolate were present but not strong. A little sweet and watery. Overall it was a decent porter a little on the light side but enjoyable.

Originally rated on 8/6/08. My second offering from the Dundee sampler 12 pack. Had a nice hoppy aroma when i opened the bottle. Poured a mid copper colored body with plenty of carbonation, with a thin off white head. Taste of hops but a little bland. Overall a fairly decent beer, and i would drink this again.

Originally rated on 8/6/08. An American style hefeweizen, the label read wheat beer so i hope i am reviewing the right beer. My first beer from Dundee out of my sampler 12 pack was interesting, It was very clear for a hefe and rather cloudy for a wheat, decent carbonation, and a thin white head. There wasnt much aroma to speak of. The taste was of a little wheat, it was kind of bland, but it wasnt offensive. Mouthfeel was o.k. a little thin, but a crisp finish. Overall a decent beer, but i probably wouldnt purchase a six pack of it.

Originally rated on 8/11/08. Out of the sampler craft case, the Dundee IPA poured a dark copper colored body, with a decent head that left heavy lacing. The aroma was floral, but faint, flavor was a little citrus, and pine but neither were very pronounced, a mildly bitter finish. It is kind of in between a IPA and a hoppy APA, A decent but not outstanding beer, it would be a good intro for those new to IPAs.

Originally rated on 8/7/08. Offering # 3 out of the 12 pack sampler. I poured a honey brown body with average carbonation, and a thin white cap that left heavy lacing. Aroma was very slight but honey and malts were present. The taste was similar to the smell while the aftertaste of honey lingered. Overall it was a pleasant beer, although it wasnt overly sweet, i wouldnt want to drink too many of these in a row, a nice change of pace beer.

Originally rated on 8/22/08. On my third as i type, I was pleasantly surprised by longhammer, partially because my expectations were not too high to begin with. It pours a dark golden yellow hue. Decent white cap disappated to a thin head, yet it leaves good lacing. Aroma of some citrus, but mostly floral, taste was similar with a lasting bitterness, and a very slight aftertaste of berries. Overall it is a pretty good IPA, especially for those new to the style, but for those seeking that super hop blast this will be an average brew.

Originally rated on 8/19/08. Have seen this one several times but never tried it until now. Kwak poured a very nice reddish orange body, With a mid sized off white cap. Aromas of spice, and a little banana. Flavors were similar but i also detected caramel and cloves, mouthfeel was smooth and sweet, a little bitter but a nice finish. Overall a pretty good beer thats worth a try.

Originally rated on 8/19/08. Thunderhead poured a medium yellow body, its mid level carbonation gave it a small white head. Mouthfeel was adequate, Aroma was very faint, a slight hop presence with no dominate floral or pine attributes. Taste was about the same as the aroma. Overall its o.k., however i wont purchase it again since there are so many other IPAs yet to try.

Originally rated on 8/17/08. An interesting brew this one. Pours a oil black body with a dark tan 1 finger cap, Aromas of expresso, burnt malts and even a little fruit, flavor followed suit with a hint of chocolate, also there was a flavor i couldnt place on the initial sip. Mouthfeel was creamy and smooth, i couldnt taste the alcohol until the last sip. The hops were the interesting part of this beer giving it the hint of fruit and a bitting aftertaste. Overall its is a good beer, thats worth a try.

Originally rated on 8/15/ 08. Bottled on 04/08. The best of the Chimay line in my humble opinion, poured a murky, deep brown body, sediment visible, with a thin light tan head, Aroma and flavors of fig, raisins, caramel, malts and a little nutty, flavor changes with the temperature. Mouthfeel is full bodied and smooth and despite the high alc. content it was hardly noticeable. Top notch brew, you gotta treat yourself from time to time

Originally rated on 8/15/08. My first beer from Allagash was a pleasant discovery. Out of batch#113 Their tripel Poured a creamy, hazy yellow, plentiful carbonation that formed a huge off white head. Aroma of fruits and spices, mostly apricot and a little plum. The taste also had the fore mentioned, but my only drawback was the alcohol it was rather noticeable but it wasnt bad. Mouthfeel was creamy and smooth even with the high alc. content. I thought it was a pretty good beer and i will purchase it again.

Originally rated on 8/14/08. Didnt know this was a bock until i just looked it up. The body looked more like an APA or even a IPA with an orangish-copper colored body, ample carbonation, with a mid sized light tan head. Aroma of spicy hops, flavor was balanced between the hops and malts, a little sweet, with hints of berries. Overall a pretty good beer no matter what style it tries to be

Originally rated on 8/13/08. McEwans scotch ale poured a deep brown body, when held to light a nice amber color appears, lightly carbonated the is a thin head. Aroma of sweet bread and malt. Flavors of the fore mentioned along with hints of chocolate, and brown sugar. Creamy mouthfeel smooth despite the 8% alc. Overall a pretty good beer.

Originally rated on 8/12/08. Samuel Smiths Taddy porter was pretty good, the dark black body had decent carbonation, and the tannish head left fair lacing. Aromas of sweet roasted malts, chocolate and coffee, flavor follows but there are hints of nuts and its a little smokey. Mouthfeel was a little on the thin side, but it was smooth and malty, easy to drink. Overall its worth a try.

Originally rated on 8/12/08. O.G. poured a dark black body, miniscule carbonation led to a tiny head. I didnt rate this beer very high because the aroma and flavor were rather strange. Almost like burnt black licorice, thats the closest thing to compare it with. It wasnt bad or offensive, just different. It was a little creamy and smooth, easy to drink. It was a decent brew, one i would probably try again to see if i could figure it out better.

Originally rated on 8/8/08.A dark black body that doesnt let any light though, a thin dark tan cap, that left minimal lacing. Aromas a plenty- oak, mocha, chocolate, and roasted nuts. All those also come through in the taste as well as oats,a nd a little smoke, with a nice bitter bite at the end. Creamy and smooth, excellent balance with this stout.

Originally rated on 8/ 6/08. After seeing this one several times i finally bought a 4 pack, at $14 its a bit steep but sometimes you get what you pay for, and I did. Celebrator pours a dark black body, even with a fair amount of carbonation the head is rather thin. Aroma of chocolate and roasted malts. Flavor of ample roasted malts, some chocolate, and coffee. It starts out slightly sweet with a mildly bitter bite and earthy finish. Havent had to many dopplebocks but this one was the best by far, so far. Their box lists all their accolades which are well deserved

Originally rated on 8/5/08. Poured a dark black body with a thin tan cap, not much aroma to speak of but there were faint hints of chocolate, and roasted coffee. Good flavors also of chocolate, roasted malts, and coffee. Mouthfeel, i thought was a little watery for a cream stout but it was still decent and smooth. Overall a pretty good beer.

Originally rated on 8/5/08. My first try at an oatmeal stout, i like oatmeal, and stouts, it sounded like an intriguing combination. It had a black body with a thin tan head. aroma of roasted malts, and coffee. Flavor also had the roasted malt, coffee and brown sugar, not any oatmeal to speak of however. Mouthfeel was creamy and was very smooth, with a sweet aftertaste. I will definatley give this another try

Originally rated on 8/4/08. It poured a dark brown body, with a light tan cap. The aroma was really nice, a mixture of cherries, apples, banana, and plum, all ripe like the bottle says. The fruit carries over into the taste, where there is also malt, yeast and a sublte sweetness that blend very well together. Even with the high alc. content it is very smooth, with a creamy mouthfeel. A beer worth seeking out for sure.

Originally rated on 8/1/08. My first and probably last gueuze, i flat out didnt like this stuff. It smelled like a old sneaker, tasted incredibly sour, and had a foul aftertaste. My palate is not used to this, nor will it be. It was rather nice looking however, it poured a hazy gloden yellow with a nice head and lots of bubbles.

Originally rated on 8/1/08.Clear golden yellow with a frothy white head. Not much aroma, tastes of a little corn and hay. A little lacing was left on my glass, overall its what you would expect, a bland, unexciting third world beer

Originally rated on 8/1/08. Pours a medium yellow body, good carbonation gives a decent white head, and a little bite. The aroma of corn and straw. Taste of grain, its a little sweet with a slightly bitter finish. Not a bad beer, but glad i got a single instead of the six pack.

Originally rated on 8/1/08. It poured a deep mohagany, amber when held up to light, with a thick tan head. There wasnt much aroma to speak of. The flavor was overwhelming of alcohol i couldnt believe that it was only 6.5%, the other flavors were cherries, roasted malt, caramel and a little chocolate, but the alcohol drowned them out. If it wasnt for that i would have rated it higher.

Originally rated on 7/31/08. Pours a medium yellow body, ample carbonation with a mid sized white cap, however it had floaters (yeast?), not common for this style. Smell of sweet malts, light hops, good lacing. Rather average beer all the way around.

Originally rated on 7/31/08. "A deep, burnt copper colored body with a thin light tan head looked rather nice, the aroma of citrus and a small amount of pine. Mouthfeel was hearty, flavor was citrus with a decent hop bite. Overall a pretty good IPA.

Originally rated on 7/31/08. This was my first kristal beer. Have to say it was pretty good. It poured a clear pale yellow body, medium carbonation, and a thick head that disappeared quickly. Aroma of cloves, nutmeg, and a little banana. Mouthfeel was good and smooth. Flavor is predominatley clove and nutmeg with a little friutiness thrown in. Overall a pretty good beer, but the sweetness would keep me from drinking several of these in a row

Originally rated on 7/31/08. The body is a clear golden yellow with ample carbonation and a 1 finger white head. Aroma of malt and grain, taste is similar to aroma with a sweet finish. Thin mouthfeel but crisp, a decent beer but not good enough to warrant another purchase

beerName: Great Divide Yeti Imperial Stout - Oak Aged
reviewBlob: Originally rated on 7/30/08. esterday I tried the yeti imp. stout, so today its the oak aged yetis turn. Like Y.I.S it pours a coal black body with a thin dark tan cap. The aroma immediatley hits you, vanilla, coffee, alcohol and a little fruit are present. The mouthfeel is thick and creamy, Flavor is complex with coffee, vanilla, chocolate and fruits all fighting for attention. Overall i like it (oak aged)better than the regular yeti, the coffee isnt as dominant, its more flavorful and smoother, you cant go wrong with either one though. Although its pricey it is a good beer thats worth your time.

brewerName: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
reviewBlob: Originally rated on 7/30/08. Big butt pours a dark amber body, with a light tan head, and medium carbonation. Aroma is very light with hints of coffee and caramel. Mouthfeel is kinda watery, not very substancial. Flavor is rather light but chocolate and roasted malts are present, it also had a slight metallic twinge. Overall its too thin, but its not bad and it is drinkable.

Originally rated on 7/29/08. Pours a decent looking clear yellow body, mid sized white cap with good carbonation. Aroma of malt, a ltlle grassy, taste was the same but it had a metallic twinge to it. Very average pilsner, at least i got brazil on my list.

Originally rated on 7/29/08. A big beer for sure, like pouring out burnt motor oil, this stuff is black and thick, a thin tan cap with a little carbonation. Aroma of roasted malts, and coffee. Falvors also of roasted malts, coffee, toffee, caramel, oh yeah and coffee. It is sweet at first giving way to hop bitterness. Overall a pretty good brew, worth a try

Pours a thick hazy yellow body with a thick white head, that leaves a fair amount of lacing. Aroma is earthy with cloves, and a little citrus. The flavor was rather strange, nothing stood out except a musty and bitter taste. The bottle says its a seasonal, dont know if its old (brewed in 08)but it should still be good. Dont know if i would try this again. Tasted on 8-27-08

Originally rated on 7/28/08. My first beer from Fullers was a good one. Flavors of fruit, spices and sweet bread were wonderful with a rich maltiness, that was balanced by a slight bitter bite. It was a rich, flavorful and complex beer, very creamy and smooth. I wish I had another one, certainly worth a try.

Originally rated on 7/28/08. My first ESB, have to say it was pretty good. It poured a deep orange- amber body, with a thin light tan head, minimal carbonation. Very creamy mouthfeel, smooth drinking, slightly bitter but not overwhelming. Flavor has slight hints of bread and raisins. Overall a pretty good beer thats worth a try.

Originally rated on 7/25/08. A deep amber body with a mid sized white cap, that left good lacing on the glass, decent carbonation. Slight aromas of rasins, spices and oranges. The flavor was o.k., the sweetness was all that really stood out, i was expecting a little more. the alcohol was well hid, and it had a good mouthfeel. Overall it was worth a try but i probably wont buy it again.

Originally rated on 7/25/08. Beer no. 5 out of the sampler case. Looks like a good hefe, smells like a good hefe, but thats about it. There wasnt much flavor, the tiny hints of orange, and corriander were barley noticeable. Mouthfeel was rather watery and thin, the carbonation gave it a little bite. A below average hefeweizen.

Originally rated on 7/24/08. My first russian beer, have to say it was pretty good. Pours a very dark body with a thin tan cap that left good lacing. Aroma of coffee, molasses, and chocolate. Flavor was similar to the aroma, it was a sweet beer that went down smoothly, nice finish, and upon finishing a pleasant little buzz. Price was good as well, I would recommend this beer.

Originally rated on 7/24/08. Its not for the faint of heart", Wow! they got that right, Im glad I had another ipa before this one, otherwise my taste buds would have been decimated if this was the first beer of the day. A deep orange-amber body, minimal carbonation with tan head, all the suspended particles made it look like my glass was dirty. Aroma was very piney and floral, it remined me of canned pineapples, very sweet. It was almost to intense to enjoy the flavors of sweet nutty malts, citrus and fruit. A little too hoppy for me, but a great beer, If you enjoy a super hopped beer this one is for you

Originally rated on 7/23/08. A very hazy golden body, a thick off white cap fueled by continuous carbonation stayed until the end. Rather complex it has hints of cloves, banana, fruits, and other spices, producing a slightly spicey-sweet flavor. A hearty beer that finishes nicely

beerName: Flying Dog Snake Dog IPA (2008 and later)
reviewBlob: Originally rated on 7/24/08. Beer no. 4 out of the sampler case. The body was amber with a slight orange tinge, fair amount of carbonation, thin head. Aroma was of piney hops, and little fruity. The beer was smooth going down with a decent bitter aftertaste. Overall an above average brew, thats worth a try.

Originally rated on 7/23/08. No. 3 out of the sampler pack, Pours a deep copper body, medium carbonation, with a rather thin cap. Decent aroma a little like juicy fruit bubble gum. Flavor carried the fruit hints, with some caramel malts as well, slight hop bite as well. Overall it is a fairly decent beer.
